The chairman of PDP in Plateau State, Chris Hassan has described the performance of his party the PDP in the just concluded bye elections in the Jos North/Bassa federal constituency and Pankshin South State constituency as a signal that the party is going to perform creditably well in the 2023 general elections on the plateau. Hassan in an interview with newsmen in Jos said his party has gained popularity and acceptability of the people of the state. Hassan added that the victory of the PDP at the bye elections has proved one thing that Plateau people believes in PDP and will go all out in 2023 to return the party back to power on the Plateau. National Convention: APC Inaugurates 20 Sub-Committees March 7 Groups Urge INEC To Review Ogoja/Yala Federal Constituency… He appreciated Plateau electorates for giving their Mandate to his party man to represent them at National Assembly. He also added that, the outcome of the Pankshin South bye election would be challenged at the tribunal considering the cancellation of votes in PDP strongholds. He called on the people of Plateau to accord greater support to his party as they prepare for campaigns and 2023 general elections in the state. He added that Plateau remains the home of PDP.